abstract: >
  OMNIA-MINIMAL is a minimal reproducible demonstration of the OMNIA ecosystem.
  It demonstrates one narrow claim: correctness is not structural stability.
  The repository shows that an output can pass surface correctness while failing
  structural stability under independent transformations. OMNIA-MINIMAL does not
  infer meaning, decide truth, or replace human judgment. It emits bounded
  post-hoc structural signals: STABLE, FRAGILE, and DIVERGENT.
